// Our game doesn't encourage sybil players, because you are not incentivized to have multiple accounts play the game,
// because the more you play, the more value your account has. Using multiple accounts does not qualify you for much play time,
// So, each of those accounts you play with holds less value compared to if you have one account that you frequently play with.
// This way, GameT prevents sybil accounts. This is helpful when we want to know how many players are playing our game. And how many players are not.
// And this value can be read from the blockchain.
